org.magelan.core
Interface EntityModifier

public interface EntityModifier

Used to drag & drop modify entities. It is supposed to modify its parent entity according to the coordinates given. The result modification is specific for each modifier: the entity can be resized, moved, etc.

The entity should provide modifiers for all of its specific points. For example a line will produce 3 modifiers:

  1. at the start of the line, which if used will result in moving the line start to the new coordinates;
  2. at the end of the line, which if used will result in moving the line end to the new coordinates;
  3. at the middle of the line, which if used will result in moving the whole line to the new coordinates.
A circle would use its modifiers to change size and position. All entities will produce modifiers with specific behaviour.

Version:
1.02, 02/2002
Author:
Assen Antov
